	<LINE>EDUCATIONAL DIRECTORY. 53</LINE>
	<LINE>The Trust embraces : —</LINE>
	<LINE>1. THE BOYS' AND GIRLS' HOSPITAL SCHOOL,</LINE>
	<LINE>The foundationers of which receive their meals at the Hospital, and</LINE>
	<LINE>Free Education, including Books. Children in St. Nicholas Parish are</LINE>
	<LINE>alone eligible. The age at admission must be not less than seven.</LINE>
	<LINE>2. THE GIRLS' HOME AND SCHOOL OF DOMESTIC ECONOMY.</LINE>
	<LINE>This Institution will be opened in the autumn of 1891. The number</LINE>
	<LINE>of foundationers is limited to 60, one half of Avhom will reside in the House ;</LINE>
	<LINE>the others will be boarded out. The subjects to be taught are Dressmak-</LINE>
	<LINE>ing, Cookery, and Laundry work. Classes will be arranged not only for</LINE>
	<LINE>foundationers and Free Scholars, but also for fee-paying pupils, and the</LINE>
	<LINE>teachers to be appointed for each of the departments will be capable of</LINE>
	<LINE>giving instruction of the highest class in all branches of their respective</LINE>
	<LINE>subjects.</LINE>
	<LINE>3. BURSARIES.</LINE>
	<LINE>Bursaries in connection with the Grammar School and Public and State-</LINE>
	<LINE>aided schools in Aberdeen are awarded annually by competitive examina-</LINE>
	<LINE>tion, and also small Scholarships for Evening Classes.</LINE>
	<LINE>Schedules of application for the benefits of the Trust may be had at the</LINE>
	<LINE>Office, Boys' and Girls' Hospital School, King street.</LINE>
